						<summary>

						<p>A broken slab lying in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Vīra-pāṇḍya Year 9:</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription may palaeographically be assigned to about the 13th century A.D. </p>						

						<p>It records the setting up of an image of Kaṟpagappiḷḷai at the western entrance of the village Pulariyūr in Aṇḍa-nāḍu and the endowment of one <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> made for maintaining a <hi rend="italic">sandhyādīpa</hi> to this deity by a person, where name is lost. But he is said to be a native of a place included in the division Pāṇḍi-maṇḍalam. A Śivabrāhmaṇa of this village and belonging to Kauśika-gōtra is stated to have received the gift of an <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> and maintained the lamp to the god.</p>						

						</summary>
